fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.themes

Interface ITemplateItem


  • public interface ITemplateItem
    Simplification of the data structure interface to provide template-friendly access to cell data.

    This simplification permits data access with the following syntax (where the exact syntax will depend on the template system implementation):

    item.CELL_NAME.value

    ...instead of the more verbose syntax:

    item.getDataFor(cellObject).getValue()

    Furthermore, implementations of this interface (that do not providing any other conflicting publicÂ getXXX() methods) avoid any conflict between cell names and properties of the full item interface (for example, the full item interface defines the modified property, which would conflict with dynamic template resolution of any cell named "modified"). In other words, implementations should avoid implementing any other interface and avoid providing any other non-default public methods.

    Thread-safety: implementations of this interface are not required to be safe for concurrent access. Therefore, processing should generally not be shared between multiple threads.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    IItem
